1.3.5
  Summary: Alignment system, alpha mutants, reactive chaining, combat mutators, expanded mutant factions
  Gameplay:
    Added: alpha mutants. Mutants that rack up kills become alphas. They hit harder, absorb more punishment, never flee, and drop bonus loot for their species. Scales with kill level. Each feature toggleable in MCM.
    Added: alpha kill retaliation. Killing an alpha triggers same-species mutants to hunt the killer.
    Added: species-based squad death responses. Predator and territorial packs avenge killed members. Herbivores and weak mobs scatter.
    Added: combat mutators via hit callbacks. Alpha hit power scales with kill level. Veteran+ stalker hit power scales from veteran to legend rank. Separate MCM toggles.
    Added: alignment system based on GSC's moral axis (principled, self-serving, unprincipled, outlaw). Military never flees, ecologists never conquer, renegades never investigate etc
    Added: mutant territorial behavior. Mutants conquer territory, avenge their dead, and hunt wounded stalkers based on personality traits.
    Changed: reactive consequences chain. A single event now triggers multiple independent responses. A squad wipe fires both revenge and retreat. A medkit use attracts predators and sends allies to help. A massacre draws scavengers and investigators.
    Changed: personality probability narrowed. Factions commit to identity-consistent behavior more often and hesitate less.
    Changed: squads stay at destinations for realistic durations to let gulag jobs (patrol, sleep, socialize etc) unfold. Previously all squads left after 5 minutes.
    Removed: stalker elites. The engine tracks stalker progression natively through kill-to-rank points.
    Removed: elite kill bounty.
  Core:
    Added: mutators MCM section with toggles for alpha and stalker combat modifiers.
	Added: tracing statistics every minute when debug is on, will help standardise log pasing from users
  i18n:
    Added: full Russian description (doc/readme_ru.txt).
    Fixed: Russian MCM synced with English.
  Fixed:
    Fixed: crash on fast travel when a scripted squad dies offline and the engine recycles its entity ID.

1.3.0
  Summary: Personality system, mutant conquest, territory decay, round-robin dispatch, ownership registry, integration framework, fixes
  Requires xlibs update.

  Gameplay:
    Added: personality profiles for all stalker and mutant factions with trait-driven consequence selection.
    Added: persistent map markers for elite promotion. Marks the elite's squad on the PDA until death.
    Added: squad ownership registry. Alife mods register an ownership filter, AlifePlus skips squads they own. Warfare and BAO registered via legacy proxies.
    Added: integration API for external mods. Register custom causes and consequences without modifying AlifePlus code.
    Added: automatic save data cleanup on version upgrade. Orphaned squads released, stale keys removed.
    Added: conquered territory decays after configurable game hours if not reconquered.
    Added: per-smart cooldown on area cause. Same location cannot trigger conquest repeatedly.
    Changed: each needs consequence tied to specific personality traits. Hunger and sleep use survival, money uses greed, jobs use territory and perception, social uses relation.
    Changed: per-consequence rate budget tightened. The same consequence type cannot dominate a session.
    Changed: post-arrival wait uses game time. Advances during time skips, survives save and load.
    Changed: squads detected as arrived faster (scan interval reduced).
    Changed: stash consequences (loot, ambush, fill) harmonized into the same config-driven pattern as needs.
    Changed: smart terrain mutation and load restore unified into a single periodic update.
    Changed: radiant interval and global consequence budget defaults adjusted for less frequent, more varied activity.
    Removed: job_worship and job_exercise consequences, MCM entries, PDA messages, and item sections.
    Removed: per-consequence chance sliders. Replaced by personality system. PDA chance sliders remain.
  Compatibility:
    Fixed: warfare and BAO ownership filters gave false positives on squads without the expected field.
  Fixed:
    Fixed: area conquest MCM toggle had no effect on previously conquered smart terrains.
    Fixed: radiant causes did not fire on first session after game start.
    Fixed: needs thresholds broke on young saves with low game time.
  Internal:
    Changed: codebase restructured into core (pipeline) and ext (domain).
    Changed: chance gate removal eliminates per-consequence random rolls from every dispatch cycle.
    Changed: protection gate no longer allocates strings below DEBUG log level.
    Changed: producer luabind crossings reduced via global xlibs caching.
    Changed: pacer retries faster on protection reject instead of burning the full interval.
    Changed: radiant and reactive pipelines use independent Bresenham counters. Reactive events no longer biased by radiant traffic volume.
    Added: consumer statistics (PIPELINE, CAUSES, DISPATCH, LIFECYCLE) logged every 60s at DEBUG. Zero cost above DEBUG.
    Changed: alignment and personality checks moved from core consumer to ap_ext_util. Core pipeline has zero domain knowledge.
    Changed: PDA sender selection and message dispatch moved from core to ap_ext_news. Core has zero ext references.
    Changed: all consequence gates (alignment, personality) run inside observe() with full tid/path tracing.
    Changed: guard clause detector recognizes multi-line guards and counts guards throughout the function body.
    Changed: rate limiting reworked with sliding window counters and per-pipeline pacing.
  xlibs (requires xlibs update):
    Added: composite squad protection guard with shared commander context.
    Added: vertex-to-level cache with zero luabind on repeat lookups.
    Changed: scripted check uses engine fields only. Mod-specific fields handled by AP ownership registry.
    Removed: dead code in squad and smart terrain modules.

1.2.3
  Summary: Radiant/reactive split, NPC protection, global cooldown, PDA rebuild, map marker split, performance, fixes
  Core:
    Added: radiant/reactive event split, world-state changes and combat events rate-limited independently (no starvation)
    Added: global radiant cooldown prevents consequence bursts in busy areas (MCM configurable)
    Changed: map marker system decoupled from tracing and optimized for performance
    Changed: consequence chances use pseudo-random distribution for uniform distribution
  Gameplay:
    Fixed: territory changes hands only after the conquering squad physically arrives
    Fixed: stashes only filled when empty, prevents stacking
    Fixed: mutant squads no longer trigger stalker stash events, filtered at cause level
    Fixed: squads no longer churn between nearby locations, with fixed TTL between radiant transitions
    Fixed: revenge only rolls against valid enemy factions 
    Fixed: elite hunters respect the protection list 
    Fixed: stash loot evaluates squad eligibility before chance roll
    Changed: default consequence chances retuned (stash_fill 15%, stash/area/needs 20%, reactive 30%)
  Compatibility:
    Changed: four protection types (permanent, active role, task target, externally scripted) verified through one unified function ensuring single source of truth
    Changed: layered NPC protection: producer rejects radiant squads before any cause evaluates, consequence search excludes all four types, tracker rejects anything that reaches script_squad
    Changed: bounty targets, hostage targets, and externally scripted squads rejected at producer level
  Map & PDA:
    Added: map markers MCM toggle, independent from debug tracing
    Changed: PDA sender rebuilt to match dynamic_news_manager best practices (friendly factions only, online NPC registry)
    Changed: PDA messages come from stalkers already in the world (no server-object lookups, no sender cache)
  MCM:
    Added: version displayed at startup (mod + xlibs)
    Changed: MCM visual refresh
    Fixed: Russian MCM encoding restored (windows-1251)
  X-Ray & xlibs:
    Added: timed events work correctly with demonized_time_events and major modpacks (globals resolve at call time)
    Added: log deadbanding suppresses repeated lines in busy areas for cleaner logs
    Added: consequence rate limit peek without consuming tokens
    Added: cleaner console output (xmath.chance diagnostic noise removed)
    Changed: find_squads distance bounds use inclusive upper
	
